1.telnet - Communicate with the destination host.
(telnet [hostname] [port])
2.whois - Get information about a website.
(whois [domain])


3.ifplugstatus - Check if the network cable is connected to a network interface.
(ifplugstatus)
4.nload - Get the network bandwidth usage.
(nload )


5.w - Get the list of users currently logged in.
(w )
6.mail - Send mail from the terminal.
(mail [options] [address])


7.ipconfig - Get IP address configuration (Windows).
(ipconfig [options])
8.ifconfig - Get IP address configuration (Unix/Linux).
(ifconfig)
9.ip - Get IP address configuration (modern Unix/Linux).
(ip [options] )


10.ping - Test the network connectivity of the system.
(ping destination)


11.nslookup - Query DNS information.
(nslookup [domain name ])
12.dig - Domain Information Groper, used to query DNS information.
(dig [domain name])
13.host - Query DNS information.
(host [domain name] )


14.wget - Download files using HTTP, HTTPS, FTP.
(wget [url])
15.curl - Transfer data to and from a server without user interaction.
(curl [url])


16.netstat - Get the network connections.
(netstat)
17.hostname - Set and view the host name of the system.
(hostname [options] [newname])


18.route - Display or update the system routing table.
(route)
19.traceroute - Troubleshoot the network and get network latency details.
(traceroute <destination>)


20.arp - Access the mapping structure of IP address to MAC address 
(Address Resolution Protocol).(arp [hostname])
21.iwconfig.to congigure wireless network properties.(
iwconfig)


22.Tcpdumpand Wireshark- Netwaork Packet capturing and Analyzing tool.
Tcpdump-Command-line tool.Captures and displays packet data directly in the terminal.
Wirshark-Graphical user interface (GUI) tool.Provides detailed packet analysis with a user-friendly interface.





